For both the 300 MeV and 400 MeV irradiation identical
target arrangements were used. The first target hit by
the beam consisted of three thin Al- and three Fe-foils
target stacks were arranged in distances of 50 mm
between each other. In each stack 19 different elements
/6<=Z<=79/  were irradiated. The targets in the stacks
were pure element foils and some composite materials
for the target elements nitrogen, oxygen, calcium,
manganese, strontium and barium. The targets were made
of high purity materials with diameters of 15.7 mm and
their thicknesses ranged from 0.036 mm up to 3.25 mm.
